"Pours a clear deep straw producing 3 fingers of frothy, white, somewhat lasting head that leaves a nice coating of clumpy, webby lace. Aroma is cracker & biscuit malts, floral, earthy, grass & lemon hops. Taste is clean & slightly dry, biscuit & grain malt, floral, grass, lemon hops balanced with just the right amount of pepper & bitter. Finish & aftertaste malty & nicely bitter balanced. Mouthfeel is light-medium bodied with moderate carbonation, smooth,  dry, mildly oily with a moderate prickle."
