"On tap at Sweetwater Taphouse in the Atlanta airport. Pours golden yellow as expected, a bit of haze and darker than other in the style, with a super creamy half finger head on top. Aroma of plastic and dusty, dry hops, not much pils malt influence on the aroma. Meh. Flavor is dirty malts, unpleasant adjunct lager flavors, light generic hop bite, some hay. Light bodied with high carbonation. Yeah, this isn't very good, even for the style I don't get very excited about in the first place."
