"3.93/5.00"
""
"Clear, pale golden, textbook Pilsner body, with lots of gentle streamers. The smell was grainy, grassy, and clean, with just a touch of canned corn. The hops were definitely abundant here, and were the first thing I noticed. They provided a spicy start, and then they turned floral, and herbal. There was a creamy finish with still lingering hops and a hint of caramel. The body was soft and silky, and the beer was easy to drink. Nicely done."
